message: Hey - did you still want to meet up? Wasn’t sure if you got my text
Feel free to text me if you’d like: 716-830-2024. Also happy to continue communicating here.
And of course, to pry stories about Ian from you.
I am genuinely excited to meet you.
No worries
Thank you for your understanding
Oh no. I’m completely free next week. I’ll send suggestions tonight or tomorrow.
But next week is a lot better for me
I’m anticipating having to work through the weekend, unfortunately. Big deadline early next week
Are you free on Saturday or Sunday? We could plan an activity?
It’s okay! I actually have plans every day the rest of the week...but another time!
I’m so sorry.

Hi! I’m so sorry for my delay. Tuesday is my worst day for meetings and I’m being sucked into things that won’t end until ~ 8:00/8:30. Can I invite you to dinner and apologize profusely to you any other day this week? I can send suggestions ahead of time and create a calendar invite.
Let me know if you’re still up for hanging out - I should be able to leave work at a normal time
I think I should be good to go out after work, assuming today is still good for you
Glad to hear it
I think he only has two categorizations of people: nice and not nice.
If not, I’m happy to reschedule to another day. Also asked Ian about you - he said that you’re a nice person.
Hi! Good morning. Are you still free after work?
Thanks! Looking forward to Tuesday
It was lovely chatting with you.
Thank you. I hope you have a good day at work tomorrow.
I’ll keep you posted on my availability
Anywhere close to the 6 would be lovely

I’m going to focus on laundry for a bit. If I promise not to talk about Ian again, can we pick somewhere on Tuesday around Nolita, soho, or chinatown? Im happy to send suggestions. Also happy to reschedule if you end up working late on Tuesday.
Anyway, I’ll tell him that you said hi, and that I shared photos with you and he will probably politely ask me not to share photos of him again
And I thought I was being unreasonable.
That’s really all I can ask for at this point, knowing you for about an hour and all
But at least I’m being honest with you
There’s a small chance
Good to know I at least have a shot
If we work hard at building something together, I may hold a higher place in my heart for you one day in the far future
I’ll stop talking about Ian. I am sorry I am so obsessed.
Considering we haven’t spoken in over a decade
I don’t know him well enough to know if he’ll be mortified, but he probably will say that it’s very weird that I was interested in seeing those pictures
Much appreciated
Right. I assembled that album for you
I’m getting that sense yeah. It’s very sweet
I was going to ask - you just did that right? You didn’t just, like, have an album of embarrassing Ian photos at the ready?
Anyway, if Ian was into dudes I would probably try to enter into a civil union with him
There are also more embarrassing photos
There are actually much better photos. I put this together in hurry
Lol wow good stuff
Here are some of my favorites https://photos.google.com/share/AF1QipM72uisPlHfyqeWZZvsvZOLbXZCG5rea_CGrH7SvtLgeC8kbSQxh1Rst0Gq_rUT9Q?key=cFByWGpYVjhFdkx1bE5tRnVfVWlPSUp5WFZXcGRR
I would be perfectly fine with that
I don’t remember much, unfortunately. No actual stories. I just remember he grew his hair out for a while so it was gigantic
Would it be impolite for me to share embarrassing photos of Ian with you?
Not yet.
Did he reply already?
Yeah I figured
Everything Ian touches turns to gold
And to answer your question. It’s too late. I already asked.
Yeah I think he was. I can’t remember if he ever made it to the big tournament of champions, but he definitely did very well at some big tournaments
Was he good at debate? I would also be happy to hear stories about Ian.
Actually, he will probably tell you I was terrible at debate - because I was
And really, if I said no, would that stop you from asking?
I doubt he’d have much to say, honestly. I think he’ll at least remember me
I’m going to visit him in a few weeks. Can I ask him about you? Will he have any horror stories?
We weren’t really close. He was always nice but had some not-as-nice friends on the team
Haven’t spoken to him since high school, admittedly
Well that’s a very funny coincidence
I spent a month with him in Ethiopia a few years ago when he was starting zenysis
I nearly started a company with him
Skepticalinvestments.biz **
This is our venture fund: skepticalinveatments.biz
We were on debate together
I went to high school with him
He’s one of my closest friends
How do you know Ian?
Oh for real? I’m at 40 Foley
Wait I’m sorry - I was being creepy and looking through your pictures again. Are you friends with Ian Webster? The picture is a little blurry but it looks like a guy named Ian Webster
My office is on centre between grand and broome.
Usually somewhere between 5:30-6:30, no later than 7:30
My week is definitely going to be a little crazy, but I might be free Tuesday night. My hours are pretty unpredictable because I just have to stay until my judge decides she’s done for the night
Maybe we could start with a coffee or dinner before we make the proposal official? Are you free this week? I play dungeons and dragons on Monday but otherwise have no plans.
I actually do. The season just ended but it will be back in the water on may 1st. I keep it at pier 40 off W. Houston.
But like, do you actually have a sailboat here?
Perfect. I’ll update my Facebook relationship status immediately.
You did not! Sold!
Or rather, is it too soon to propose? I won’t cook or clean, and my life’s ambition is to do nothing, but it’s New York and did I mention that have a sailboat?
Yes, including the beautiful part
Could say the same to you
Ok. So you’re hard working, highly intelligent, well educated, eloquent, a cat owner, have access to a dog, and beautiful. I don’t quite understand what you’re doing here.
That’s a much more impressive humble brag than my startup.
That means we hear all kinds of cases
So my judge sits on the second circuit court of appeals, one step down from the Supreme Court
That sounds important. What type of cases do you typically work on?
Plus recommendations for disposition
Yes
Anyway
Assuming you even saw it...
Haha
I didn’t mean to like that message just now
They’re summaries of cases for judges, right?
Only very generally. I’m just working on bench memos for the next sitting - did your friend tell you about bench memos?
Can you tell me about your project?
I will never employ people again.
I haven’t described what I actually do! My title is CTO but what I actually do is make PowerPoint presentations, speak to attorneys, and deal with HR issues. It’s a fantastic existence.
Sure
There’s more?
And ... should I keep going?
Wow that was a lot
At some point I would like to quit my job and finish my PhD, or do nothing at all.
I also have a small payroll company that actually is profitable but only slightly, and the rest of my life is being consumed by an apartment renovation.

Outside of my startup, I have a few side projects including a popular dinosaur website and tiny venture fund that for all intents and purposes is a dumpster fire which consumes all of my extra capital and leaves nothing in return except for misery, sadness, unrealizable dreams, and the broken promise of hope.
I started the company at the end of 2013. We employ 18 people and lose a lot of venture capital.
But, ultimately auction houses are the arbiters of price (pricing reflexivity) and there’s only so much we can do.

The data problems are most interesting to me. We attempt to price something that exists in a very high dimensional space but is also extremely sparse in terms of both features and time (works often sell only once or twice). Currently, the entire market operates with qualitative pricing where an expert will look at a piece, search for comps, and make some judgment about a works value. We have automated this process to the point where we can achieve  superhuman accuracy, and are several orders of magnitude better in terms of speed, scale, and cost.

Here is some technobabble / marketing speak: My company exists at the intersection of art and finance. We gather art market data and build models to predict value and liquidity risk of fine art. We use this technology to execute on a basket of financial strategies and sell mostly to auction houses and investment banks.
Well now I’m curious to know the difference, so both I guess
Would you like the sales pitch or would you like to know what we actually do?
Yes haha I really want to know
Are you sure?
Thank god we don’t have a common law legal system.
Yes, now you have to talk about the thing you absolutely did not want to humble brag about

I am curious though

Hey you promised not to talk about your startup

I think I needed to relax a little. Going in bright and early tomorrow
I was supposed to work all day/night, but my brain had other plans. So we just finished watching a movie

her life is interesting.
